<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-03T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-03T18:00:00-05:00" n="560" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d560">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.1631/112: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-03T17:00:00-06:00">May 3, 1935—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 7:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>25. With reference to the Department’s telegram 26, May 1, noon, schedule
                            I and <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> were handed to the Salvadoran
                            Government today.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>